00:57:34,184 --> 00:57:35,886
- Hello?
- Orystal?

739
00:57:35,953 --> 00:57:39,256
I got it. Let's just meet at the
Promenade and get this over with.

740
00:57:39,289 --> 00:57:43,327
I don't know how we got here,
but I just wanted to say I'm sorry.

741
00:57:46,296 --> 00:57:47,731
My dad would probably say

742
00:57:47,798 --> 00:57:50,300
there's some great
cosmic reason for all this.

743
00:57:50,367 --> 00:57:52,436
And we'll all be better people, right?

744
00:57:52,503 --> 00:57:54,938
Well, I don't know.

745
00:57:55,906 --> 00:57:57,908
My dad also says I'm crazy.

746
00:57:57,975 --> 00:58:01,078
Dean, you're not crazy.

747
00:58:04,114 --> 00:58:06,950
There are several major book chains
around the country

748
00:58:07,017 --> 00:58:10,053
that would probably
disagree with you on that point.

749
00:58:10,120 --> 00:58:13,757
I'm my dad's favorite subject and...

750
00:58:15,192 --> 00:58:16,760
I have to go.

751
00:58:16,960 --> 00:58:18,996
- Dean.
- I'll meet you at the mall.

752
00:58:23,066 --> 00:58:24,535
It's just a beer, Mom.

753
00:58:24,568 --> 00:58:27,671
You don't have to explain
yourself to me. I trust you.

754
00:58:29,439 --> 00:58:32,543
I wonder what that would be like.

755
00:58:32,609 --> 00:58:35,245
If we could just switch roles and...

756
00:58:35,312 --> 00:58:39,516
...you could be the parent
and I would be the child

757
00:58:39,583 --> 00:58:41,885
and you could tell me what to do

758
00:58:41,952 --> 00:58:44,955
and I would listen to you
and I would trust you.

759
00:58:46,156 --> 00:58:47,691
Are you OK?

760
00:58:52,930 --> 00:58:55,165
I'm supposed to be making
a casserole now

761
00:58:55,232 --> 00:58:57,067
for Troy's memorial service.

762
00:58:57,134 --> 00:58:59,169
I don't know
what's wrong with me.

763
00:58:59,236 --> 00:59:03,974
My basic energy level's
been noticeably low lately.

764
00:59:14,084 --> 00:59:16,453
Mom, I'm sorry.

765
00:59:16,520 --> 00:59:18,689
- I have to go.
- Nope.

766
00:59:18,755 --> 00:59:21,758
Do not explain yourself to me,
I told you not to do that.

767
01:00:09,139 --> 01:00:11,608
F-17 Tigershark.

768
01:00:12,843 --> 01:00:14,545
He's here.

769
01:00:27,291 --> 01:00:28,992
Took you long enough.

770
01:00:29,927 --> 01:00:32,362
Here, this is
everything Troy had.

771
01:00:35,365 --> 01:00:37,334
Is this the kid?

772
01:00:37,367 --> 01:00:39,903
Yeah, that's him.

773
01:00:39,970 --> 01:00:42,840
- All right, let's go.
- All right.

774
01:00:42,906 --> 01:00:44,541
Fine.

775
01:00:45,943 --> 01:00:48,278
Wait a minute. Wait.

776
01:00:48,312 --> 01:00:51,348
- What?
- What is this shit?

777
01:00:51,415 --> 01:00:54,351
- What? It's all there.
- VeggiForce?

778
01:00:55,519 --> 01:00:58,088
- What are you doing?
- Yeah, this whole bag here.

779
01:00:58,155 --> 01:01:00,190
You trying to give me
stupid vitamins?

780
01:01:00,257 --> 01:01:02,860
They're notjust vitamins.
No, no.

781
01:01:02,926 --> 01:01:05,896
This is an entirely new life system.

782
01:01:11,001 --> 01:01:13,170
Billy, leave him alone.

783
01:01:13,237 --> 01:01:14,771
- Kick his ass.
- Shit.

784
01:01:14,838 --> 01:01:16,940
Billy, get off of him.

785
01:01:30,387 --> 01:01:33,157
Stop! Stop it.
What are you doing to him?

786
01:01:33,223 --> 01:01:35,459
- That dude's crazy.
- I saw the whole thing.

787
01:01:35,526 --> 01:01:38,462
- He started hitting for no reason.
- Let go of me!

788
01:01:38,529 --> 01:01:40,864
Get off of me!

789
01:01:40,931 --> 01:01:43,433
You stay right here.
Honey, honey call the cops.

790
01:01:43,500 --> 01:01:46,270
Orystal! Hey!

791
01:01:46,336 --> 01:01:49,606
Get off of me! Orystal!

792
01:02:15,666 --> 01:02:19,403
OK, so, now, you want to tell me
about this fight at the mall?

793
01:02:19,469 --> 01:02:21,104
No, not really.

794
01:02:21,171 --> 01:02:24,041
Dean, make an effort for me, please.

795
01:02:24,107 --> 01:02:27,544
I'm sure there is a reasonable
explanation for this, officer.

796
01:02:27,611 --> 01:02:29,646
I'm all ears.

797
01:02:29,713 --> 01:02:32,216
Dean?

798
01:02:33,884 --> 01:02:35,819
The guy at the mall was Billy.

799
01:02:35,886 --> 01:02:38,956
He and the other two forced me
to steal drugs from Troy.

800
01:02:39,022 --> 01:02:40,891
Troy? Who's this Troy?

801
01:02:40,958 --> 01:02:45,062
- Troy Johnson. He's dead.
- He committed suicide, sir.

802
01:02:46,530 --> 01:02:47,598
I don't understand.

803
01:02:47,664 --> 01:02:51,535
I told them no, so to force me to do it,
they kidnapped my brother.

804
01:02:51,602 --> 01:02:54,671
Wait, are you kidding me?
You got a son who's kidnapped?

805
01:02:54,738 --> 01:02:57,474
No, wait a second, listen.
They got the wrong kid.

806
01:02:57,541 --> 01:03:01,211
They said if I didn't get the stuff
from Troy, they were gonna kill him.

807
01:03:01,278 --> 01:03:03,947
- You just said Troy was dead.
- He is, officer.

808
01:03:04,014 --> 01:03:07,384
- Dean...
- So I did it, only Oharlie...

809
01:03:07,417 --> 01:03:11,021
...my little brother, Oharlie,
switched the drugs on me.

810
01:03:11,088 --> 01:03:13,757
And I wound up with a bag
of my mom's VeggiForce.

811
01:03:13,824 --> 01:03:16,660
- VeggiForce?
- It's this vitamin line that she hocks.

812
01:03:16,727 --> 01:03:19,163
VeggiForce! I know that stuff.

813
01:03:19,229 --> 01:03:21,465
Right, I know, VeggiForce, right. OK.

814
01:03:21,532 --> 01:03:24,735
Yeah. You don't know,
do they make a weight gainer for kids?

815
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:28,105
- I could check, I guess.
- Anyway, that's why we got in a fight.

816
01:03:28,172 --> 01:03:30,674
- 'Oause he wouldn't let the kid go.
- Which kid?

817
01:03:30,741 --> 01:03:32,242
The kid who was kidnapped.

818
01:03:32,309 --> 01:03:35,212
OK. I think I understand.

819
01:03:35,279 --> 01:03:37,781
You were fighting
with a guy who's kidnapping

820
01:03:37,848 --> 01:03:40,350
and drug smuggling
with a guy who killed himself.

821
01:03:40,417 --> 01:03:42,820
- Yeah.
- Well, that's great, Dean, you know?

822
01:03:42,886 --> 01:03:46,456
Only there don't happen to be
any reports around here of missing kids,

823
01:03:46,523 --> 01:03:49,193
so how do you explain that?

824
01:03:49,893 --> 01:03:53,330
I can't. I can't explain that.

825
01:03:53,397 --> 01:03:56,266
Officer, can I...?

826
01:03:56,333 --> 01:03:59,069
What's his name,
this missing kid? What's his name?

827
01:03:59,136 --> 01:04:00,671
- Oharlie.
- Oharlie what?

828
01:04:00,737 --> 01:04:03,540
Officer Bratley,
could you step outside a minute?

829
01:04:03,607 --> 01:04:06,510
- I'd like to talk to you in private.
- Officer Bratley?

830
01:04:06,577 --> 01:04:08,212
Oan you make
some sense out of this?

831
01:04:08,278 --> 01:04:11,815
- I believe I can, yes.
- All right.

832
01:04:13,183 --> 01:04:16,053
- You stay put.
- Yeah.

833
01:04:47,084 --> 01:04:49,086
I kinda wanna go home now.

834
01:04:51,655 --> 01:04:54,458
I'm not having fun anymore.

835
01:05:07,604 --> 01:05:08,972
Billy.

836
01:05:19,149 --> 01:05:21,652
Well, at least
let me set you a plate.

837
01:05:25,255 --> 01:05:28,125
Listen, I spoke to a colleague
of mine at the hospital.

838
01:05:28,192 --> 01:05:31,495
These are a stronger version
of what I've already given you,

839
01:05:31,562 --> 01:05:34,064
but, listen,
they're perfectly safe, OK, pal?

840
01:05:46,076 --> 01:05:49,046
Look, Terri, if I could
just talk to you here.

841
01:05:49,112 --> 01:05:51,882
Michael, I'm just gonna take a bath, OK?

842
01:05:51,949 --> 01:05:55,285
- It's been a long day.
- Terri, we have to talk!

843
01:05:55,352 --> 01:05:59,022
Michael, I have done absolutely
everything to prepare for our wedding.

844
01:05:59,089 --> 01:06:01,425
Everything!
All you have to do is show up.

845
01:06:01,492 --> 01:06:03,861
OK? That's it. Show up.

846
01:06:07,564 --> 01:06:11,134
Please don't leave me,
please don't leave me.

847
01:06:14,838 --> 01:06:18,375
- You are gonna listen to me.
- No.

848
01:06:18,442 --> 01:06:19,776
It's about the day we met.

849
01:06:21,678 --> 01:06:23,814
There's something
I never told you.

850
01:06:30,787 --> 01:06:32,422
Have you seen my son, Oharlie?

851
01:06:32,489 --> 01:06:36,693
Hillside is growing.
And this is what it's all about.

852
01:06:36,760 --> 01:06:41,098
This new Ocean Orest development
is exactly what...

853
01:06:49,273 --> 01:06:52,309
I am so sorry about this, Mr. Mayor.

854
01:06:53,277 --> 01:06:54,478
Michael.

855
01:06:55,913 --> 01:06:57,314
I'm Terri.

856
01:06:57,381 --> 01:07:01,218
Bratley,
from Terri's Interior Visions and...

857
01:07:01,285 --> 01:07:04,755
...I actually designed all of this.

858
01:07:04,822 --> 01:07:07,224
Wonderful.

859
01:07:16,834 --> 01:07:20,771
I feel... I feel so different.

860
01:07:39,356 --> 01:07:41,758
Look at this. The footprints...

861
01:07:41,825 --> 01:07:43,694
- Yeah?
- Look, it's like...

862
01:07:43,760 --> 01:07:46,864
- Yeah, look at this.
- Like dolphins.

863
01:07:46,930 --> 01:07:49,266
Dolphins, that's right.

864
01:07:49,333 --> 01:07:50,834
Dolphin.

865
01:08:02,913 --> 01:08:08,252
"To begin, each of us alike,
to actually conjure magic.

866
01:08:09,186 --> 01:08:13,991
This must finally be our goal
as free-willed beings.

867
01:08:14,491 --> 01:08:18,896
The joyous acceptance
of a pure state of synchronicity,

868
01:08:18,962 --> 01:08:24,368
through the seemingly random
happy accidents of our lives. "

869
01:08:26,136 --> 01:08:27,171
Don't you see?

870
01:08:28,105 --> 01:08:29,540
Nothing is random.

871
01:08:29,606 --> 01:08:34,144
Nothing happens by chance.
There is a power at work here.

872
01:08:34,211 --> 01:08:36,980
A power greater than all of us.

873
01:08:38,849 --> 01:08:41,718
Don't you see what this means?

874
01:08:44,788 --> 01:08:46,757
I just love you so much.

875
01:08:53,897 --> 01:08:55,866
I was so scared.

876
01:09:01,672 --> 01:09:03,807
Tomorrow...

877
01:09:03,874 --> 01:09:07,077
...I'll show you everything.

878
01:09:55,159 --> 01:09:56,793
Yes, I am Dr. Stiffle. Yeah.

879
01:09:56,860 --> 01:09:59,796
You know my book?
So you've heard of me?

880
01:09:59,863 --> 01:10:01,965
And my book.

881
01:10:02,032 --> 01:10:05,435
Yes, yes. I see that
you are familiar with my work.

882
01:11:12,803 --> 01:11:16,974
"To actually conjure magic. "

883
01:13:17,261 --> 01:13:19,796
- Terri?
- Honey.

884
01:13:24,601 --> 01:13:26,203
Now, do you see my vision?

885
01:13:35,012 --> 01:13:37,381
Dean, Oharlie, breakfast.

886
01:13:50,928 --> 01:13:53,630
- It's not coming off.
- I thought you understood.

887
01:13:53,697 --> 01:13:57,468
Do we have any paint thinner?
Go to the garage and look for some.

888
01:13:57,534 --> 01:13:59,403
- Paint thinner.
- Paint thinner?

889
01:13:59,470 --> 01:14:01,238
Or maybe some white paint?

890
01:14:01,305 --> 01:14:04,408
We'll just put a coat
of white paint over all of it...

891
01:14:04,441 --> 01:14:07,177
- And no one'll see it.
- You're not making any sense.

892
01:14:07,244 --> 01:14:10,981
- Why in the world would you do that?
- Don't answer it.

893
01:14:11,048 --> 01:14:13,917
- Don't answer it.
- You need to calm down.

894
01:14:16,119 --> 01:14:18,655
- Where's the beautiful bride?
- Hello. Oome in.

895
01:14:20,023 --> 01:14:22,226
How wonderful, the dress.

896
01:15:05,369 --> 01:15:08,639
Guys, I really need to
talk to you about something.

897
01:15:08,739 --> 01:15:10,407
Where are the keys?

898
01:15:10,474 --> 01:15:12,376
It's about that kid, Oharlie.

899
01:15:12,409 --> 01:15:15,646
I think we kinda kidnapped him.

900
01:15:15,712 --> 01:15:17,080
Here they are.

901
01:15:17,114 --> 01:15:19,483
That's not funny, Lee.

902
01:15:20,617 --> 01:15:21,852
Listen to me!

903
01:15:21,919 --> 01:15:24,354
We've had him since Friday.

904
01:15:25,122 --> 01:15:27,758
I don't know what to do.

905
01:15:27,825 --> 01:15:31,028
All right, let's just calm down.
I'm sure you didn't have a part

906
01:15:31,094 --> 01:15:33,330
of whatever those kids
are doing down there.

907
01:15:33,397 --> 01:15:36,767
Itjust started out as a joke. I didn't
think Billy was really gonna do it.

908
01:15:36,834 --> 01:15:38,869
- A joke?
- Wait a minute.

909
01:15:38,936 --> 01:15:41,171
Is this a kidnapping or not?

910
01:15:41,238 --> 01:15:43,407
That sort of thing
doesn't happen around here.

911
01:15:43,474 --> 01:15:45,676
If it is,
I'm going to have to call the police.

912
01:15:45,742 --> 01:15:47,644
- The police?
- In our home?

913
01:15:47,711 --> 01:15:49,646
Just a minute.
I'm talking to Lee.

914
01:15:49,713 --> 01:15:53,484
Lee, is it a joke or not?

915
01:15:54,985 --> 01:15:57,921
No. It's nothing.

916
01:15:57,988 --> 01:16:00,891
No, you don't have to call anybody.

917
01:16:02,726 --> 01:16:05,829
Well, I, for one,
did not find that very funny at all.

918
01:16:05,896 --> 01:16:07,898
And neither would a top-tier school.

919
01:16:07,965 --> 01:16:10,534
You guys, just go.

920
01:16:10,601 --> 01:16:13,137
Everything is totally fine.

921
01:16:13,203 --> 01:16:14,805
Our little man.

922
01:16:16,306 --> 01:16:19,643
Yeah, we'll always be here for you.

923
01:16:21,211 --> 01:16:24,915
I don't know why
it came to me as a dolphin.

924
01:16:24,982 --> 01:16:29,186
It's just a sign.
It could have been anything.

925
01:16:29,253 --> 01:16:32,222
But now I'm aware
of a connection

926
01:16:32,289 --> 01:16:34,224
that I didn't
even know was missing.

927
01:16:34,291 --> 01:16:36,760
Maybe we've all been missing it.

928
01:16:36,827 --> 01:16:38,796
Lou, I'm so glad you're here.

929
01:16:38,862 --> 01:16:41,832
- We need to talk.
- Now is not a good time.

930
01:16:41,899 --> 01:16:44,768
Talk to Lou. We need
to get some closure here.

931
01:16:44,835 --> 01:16:47,404
Olosure? Where's Oharlie?
Where is he?

932
01:16:47,471 --> 01:16:50,174
Excuse me, could you help me
hold up this end, please?

933
01:16:50,240 --> 01:16:52,209
Hey, I'm getting married today.

934
01:16:52,276 --> 01:16:55,412
I love Michael now,
I thought I made that perfectly clear.

935
01:16:57,815 --> 01:16:59,983
- Where is Oharlie?
- I don't know...

936
01:17:00,050 --> 01:17:03,320
- Why don't you know? Is he missing?
- No, he's not missing!

937
01:17:03,353 --> 01:17:06,290
- Where is he?
- He is just out gallivanting.

938
01:17:06,356 --> 01:17:09,259
Gosh, darn it, honey,
you pierced his dorsal.

939
01:17:11,995 --> 01:17:14,465
Let's see some fuckin' blood, already.

940
01:17:25,642 --> 01:17:30,080
I probably would've been with some
football player, if I hadn't met you.

941
01:17:30,147 --> 01:17:34,218
And I guess I just want to thank you
for keeping it interesting for me.

942
01:17:34,284 --> 01:17:37,421
It's definitely not the usual thing.

943
01:17:37,488 --> 01:17:40,090
Who wants that, right?

944
01:17:40,157 --> 01:17:42,426
What the fuck
are you talking about?

945
01:17:42,493 --> 01:17:44,728
Let's just stop, Billy.

946
01:17:44,795 --> 01:17:48,098
Let's just quit this thing with Oharlie,
forget about the pills.

947
01:17:48,198 --> 01:17:51,235
And everything. Let's just stop.

948
01:17:51,301 --> 01:17:53,203
OK?

949
01:17:53,270 --> 01:17:55,672
It's over.

950
01:17:56,707 --> 01:17:58,242
Sit down!

951
01:18:04,047 --> 01:18:07,251
Guess it doesn't matter what you think.

952
01:18:08,452 --> 01:18:10,020
Lee.

953
01:18:17,060 --> 01:18:19,463
Good. Sit right down,
what can I get you?

954
01:18:19,530 --> 01:18:22,099
Oharlie, Bill!
It's getting cold.

955
01:18:24,401 --> 01:18:25,669
Good morning.

956
01:18:25,736 --> 01:18:28,605
Do you think that's appropriate
for a memorial service?

957
01:18:28,672 --> 01:18:31,175
I think I'll shoot on over
to the wedding instead.

958
01:18:31,241 --> 01:18:32,810
What are you talking about?

959
01:18:32,876 --> 01:18:35,579
I covered death
extensively in my first two books.

960
01:18:35,646 --> 01:18:38,482
I've done grieving to death.

961
01:18:38,549 --> 01:18:40,784
Maybe I'll get a few insights
at the wedding.

962
01:18:40,851 --> 01:18:43,654
Multiple marriage couples.
Gotta be a new book in there.

963
01:18:43,720 --> 01:18:46,223
How is it going to look
if we don't go to the memorial?

964
01:18:46,290 --> 01:18:48,458
If it means that much,
you go ahead and go.

965
01:18:48,525 --> 01:18:50,594
We should all go
together as a family.

966
01:18:50,661 --> 01:18:54,665
I understand your feelings. Maybe
you could make the same effort for me.

967
01:18:54,731 --> 01:18:56,934
Dean, it looks like
you have a choice to make.

968
01:18:57,000 --> 01:19:00,070
The wedding with him
or the memorial with me.

969
01:19:00,137 --> 01:19:04,208
Dean, it's your decision,
him or me.

970
01:19:04,274 --> 01:19:06,143
I think it's best
if he stayed home today.

971
01:19:06,243 --> 01:19:08,812
He can make up his mind.
He's practically an adult.

972
01:19:08,879 --> 01:19:12,783
As a therapist, it's my opinion
that he should avoid anything upsetting.

973
01:19:12,850 --> 01:19:16,820
As a mother, it's fucking important he
learn how to function in the real world.

974
01:19:16,887 --> 01:19:20,424
I'm not going to get into an argument
with you now.

975
01:19:20,491 --> 01:19:23,494
Let's not argue.
Let's sit down and have a meal together.

976
01:20:15,379 --> 01:20:17,381
- Hello?
- Hi, is Dean here?

977
01:20:18,549 --> 01:20:21,518
- It's for school.
- Well, go ahead then.

978
